yodl version 3.05.01

Your Own Document Language

Usage: yodl [OPTION]... [FILE]...
Convert to various documentation formats from FILE or <stdin>.

Options:
  -D, --define=NAME[=VALUE]
                       define NAME as a symbol, same as DEFINESYMBOL(NAME)()
                       If `=VALUE' is added, NAME receives VALUE as its
                       initial value, same as DEFINESYMBOL(NAME)(VALUE)
  -d, --definemacro=NAME=EXPANSION
                       define NAME as macro expanding to EXPANSION
  -h, --help           this message
  -i, --index[=file]   `file' is the name of the index file. By default
                       <outputbase>.idx is used. No default for stdout.
  -I, --include=DIR    use directory DIR for system-wide includes files
                         [.:/usr/local/share/yodl-3.05.01]
  -k, --keep-ws        When WSLEVEL is non-zero, keep ws at line-heads
                       unless lines are terminated by \
  -l, --live-data=HOW  set "live data" policy to HOW [none]:
                         execute SYSTEM and PIPETHROUGH commands:
                           `none' or `0':    never (the default)
                           `confirm' or `1': only when confirmed
                           `report' or `2':  issuing warning
                           `ok' or `3':      always
  -L, --legacy-include do NOT change working directory when including a
                       Yodl file located in another directory
  -m, --messages=SET   set message level to a combination of SET acdeinw:
                          a: alert,    c: crit,    d: debug,
                          e: error,    i: info,    n: notice,
                          w: warning
  -n, --max-nested-files=NR set the maximum number of nested files that
                       can be parsed to NR [20]
  -o, --output=FILE    send output to FILE instead of <stdout>
  -p, --preload=CMD    preload CMD
  -r, --max-replacements=NR set the maximum number of macros or substs
                       per character read from file to NR x 10,000 [1]
                       (--max-replacements=0 implies no maximum)
  -t, --trace          trace generated output to <stderr> for each parsing pass
  -V, --version        show Yodl's version
  -v, --verbose        increase verbosity (-vv...)
  -W, --warranty       show warranty and copyright
  -w, --warn           warn about no-macro calls

